subject: Potential confusion for Steam
text:
The Steam summary lists both "No Right to leave the service" and "A user can voluntarily cancel their account at any time". While (after reviewing) I can see a subtle distinction, it is not very clear. Perhaps the first should be "no right to have information deleted".
